    • Uses of FlowEvent in com.solacesystems.solclientj.core

      Methods in com.solacesystems.solclientj.core that return FlowEvent 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      static FlowEvent Solclient.Allocator.newFlowEvent()
      Allocates a new FlowEvent, this instance is to be used with the FlowHandle.takeFlowEvent() method.

    • Uses of FlowEvent in com.solacesystems.solclientj.core.handle

      Methods in com.solacesystems.solclientj.core.handle that return FlowEvent 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      FlowEvent FlowHandle.getFlowEvent()
      This method returns a FlowEvent instance in the context of FlowEventCallback.onEvent().
      Methods in com.solacesystems.solclientj.core.handle with parameters of type FlowEvent 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void FlowHandle.takeFlowEvent(FlowEvent flowEvent, boolean withInfoString)
      This method clones the last FlowEvent into the given FlowEvent The given FlowEvent is implementation specific and is expected to be the one produced by Allocator.newFlowEvent() This call is valid while on the same thread and in context of FlowEventCallback.onEvent().
